Chusyā Bāhāḥ; floor plan by Wolfgang Korn; ca. 1969; free access - no reuse; source: Korn, The Traditional Architecture of Nepal, 1975, p. 49.
mapsanddrawingsdescription: This floor plan does not show the two caityas that flank Vajrasatva in the present-day. The miniature stone temple of Mañjuśrī that was moved to the courtyard in 1970 CE, is also missing. Considering that Wolfgang Korn first came to Nepal in 1968 CE, it is most likely that the survey of the courtyard was conducted in circa 1969 CE.
